"i": 615, "t": "F98.4"}, {"i": 616, "t": "STEREOTYPED MOVEMENT DISORDER"}, {"i": 617, "t": "F99"}, {"i": 618, "t": "UNSPECIFIED MENTAL DISORDER"}, {"i": 619, "t": "in progress"}, {"i": 620, "t": "ICD-10 CODE NOT ASSIGNED"}, {"i": 621, "t": "SYMPTOM DOMAINS OF PRIMARY PSYCHOTIC DISORDERS"}, {"i": 622, "t": "PREMENSTRUAL DYSPHORIC DISORDER (PMDD)"}, {"i": 623, "t": "PERSONALITY DIFFICULTY"}, {"i": 624, "t": "OBSTRUCTIVE SLEEP APNOEA (OSA)"}, {"i": 625, "t": "NARCOLEPSY"}, {"i": 626, "t": "‹ SUBSTANCE-RELATED"}, {"i": 627, "t": "ICD-11"}, {"i": 628, "t": "6C50"}, {"i": 629, "t": "BEHAVIOURAL ADDICTIONS (GAMBLING, GAMING)"}, {"i": 630, "t": "Gambling Disorder,"}, {"i": 631, "t": "ICD-10"}, {"i": 632, "t": "F63.0"}, {"i": 633, "t": "BEHAVIOURAL ADDICTIONS (GAMBLING, GAMING)"}, {"i": 634, "t": "DSM-5-TR"}, {"i": 635, "t": "BEHAVIOURAL ADDICTIONS (GAMBLING, GAMING)"}, {"i": 636, "t": "Definition and nosology"}, {"i": 637, "t": "History"}, {"i": 638, "t": "epidemiology"}, {"i": 639, "t": "Aetiology and pathogenesis"}, {"i": 640, "t": "clinical picture"}, {"i": 641, "t": "diagnosis"}, {"i": 642, "t": "Examination and assessment"}, {"i": 643, "t": "treatment"}, {"i": 644, "t": "prognosis"}, {"i": 645, "t": "Myths and misconceptions"}, {"i": 646, "t": "Sources"}, {"i": 647, "t": "1. Definition and nosology"}, {"i": 648, "t": "Behavioural addictions (ICD-11:"}, {"i": 649, "t": "6C50"}, {"i": 650, "t": "Gambling Disorder,"}, {"i": 651, "t": "6C51"}, {"i": 652, "t": "Gaming Disorder; DSM-5-TR: 312.31 Gambling Disorder) — a persistent or recurrent pattern of gambling or video-gaming behaviour with impaired control; it causes significant functional impairment."}, {"i": 653, "t": "2. History"}, {"i": 654, "t": "DSM-IV (1994) — \"Pathological Gambling\" within the impulse control disorders."}, {"i": 655, "t": "DSM-5 (2013) — \"Gambling Disorder\" was moved to the substance use and addiction category (similar neurobiology)."}, {"i": 656, "t": "ICD-11 (2019) —"}, {"i": 657, "t": "Gaming Disorder"}, {"i": 658, "t": "(gaming addiction) added as an official category."}, {"i": 659, "t": "3. Epidemiology"}, {"i": 660, "t": "Gambling Disorder lifetime prevalence: 0.2–5.3% (wide range)."}, {"i": 661, "t": "Gaming Disorder: 1–10% (Europe) among young people."}, {"i": 662, "t": "Sex: gambling is more prevalent in men; the sex difference narrows in online gambling; gaming predominates in men."}, {"i": 663, "t": "Comorbidity: MDD, anxiety, other substance use, ADHD, BPD, suicide risk."}, {"i": 664, "t": "4. Aetiology and pathogenesis"}, {"i": 665, "t": "Heritability 50–60%."}, {"i": 666, "t": "Neurobiological — dysregulation of the reward circuit (dopamine), similar to substance use disorders."}, {"i": 667, "t": "Personality — impulsivity, sensation-seeking."}, {"i": 668, "t": "5. Clinical picture"}, {"i": 669, "t": "Persistent/recurrent behaviour (gambling, gaming)."}, {"i": 670, "t": "Loss of control."}, {"i": 671, "t": "Occupational, family, social, and academic impairment."}, {"i": 672, "t": "\"Chasing losses\" (in gambling) — attempts to win back losses."}, {"i": 673, "t": "Lying, financial disruption (gambling), online preoccupation (gaming)."}, {"i": 674, "t": "Comorbid MDD and high suicide risk."}, {"i": 675, "t": "6. Diagnosis"}, {"i": 676, "t": "6.1 Unified diagnostic criteria"}, {"i": 677, "t": "Gambling (DSM-5-TR):"}, {"i": 678, "t": "≥ 4 of 9 symptoms within a 12-month period:"}, {"i": 679, "t": "Gambling with increasing amounts — tolerance;"}, {"i": 680, "t": "Irritability or restlessness when cutting down gambling — withdrawal;"}, {"i": 681, "t": "Unsuccessful attempts to cut down;"}, {"i": 682, "t": "Preoccupation with gambling;"}, {"i": 683, "t": "Gambling when distressed;"}, {"i": 684, "t": "\"Chasing\" after losses;"}, {"i": 685, "t": "Lying;"}, {"i": 686, "t": "Loss of relationships/job;"}, {"i": 687, "t": "Reliance on financial bailouts."}, {"i": 688, "t": "Gaming (ICD-11):"}, {"i": 689, "t": "Over a 12-month period: impaired control, increasing priority given to gaming, a continuing/escalating course + functional impairment."}, {"i": 690, "t": "6.2 Source-specific clarifications"}, {"i": 691, "t": "WHO — Gaming Disorder is official."}, {"i": 692, "t": "APA — Internet Gaming Disorder in DSM-5 Section III for further study."}]